Caisse DE Depot ET Placement DU Quebec Cuts Position in Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd. (NASDAQ:NCLH)

					Posted by Danessa Lincoln on Jul 22nd, 2017 // No Comments 




Caisse DE Depot ET Placement DU Quebec lowered its position in  Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd. (NASDAQ:NCLH) by 79.2% during the first quarter, according to its most recent 13F filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission (SEC). The fund owned 9,870 shares of the company’s stock after selling 37,630 shares during the period. Caisse DE Depot ET Placement DU Quebec’s holdings in Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings were worth $501,000 as of its most recent filing with the SEC. 
A number of other large investors have also added to or reduced their stakes in the company. Norges Bank purchased a new position in shares of  Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings during the fourth quarter worth approximately $34,688,000.  Thrivent Financial for Lutherans purchased a new position in shares of  Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings during the fourth quarter worth approximately $5,051,000.  Guggenheim Capital LLC raised its position in shares of  Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings by 169.1% in the fourth quarter. Guggenheim Capital LLC now owns 134,298 shares of the company’s stock worth $5,712,000 after buying an additional 84,383 shares during the last quarter.  Seven Eight Capital LP purchased a new position in shares of  Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings during the fourth quarter worth approximately $110,000.  Finally, First Republic Investment Management Inc. raised its position in shares of  Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings by 7.9% in the fourth quarter. First Republic Investment Management Inc. now owns 7,880 shares of the company’s stock worth $336,000 after buying an additional 575 shares during the last quarter. Institutional investors and hedge funds own  85.94% of the company’s stock. 


 Get Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd. alerts:



Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd. (NASDAQ:NCLH) traded up 0.04% during mid-day trading on Friday, hitting $55.07. The company had a trading volume of 665,799 shares. The company’s 50 day moving average price is $53.35 and its 200-day moving average price is $50.49. The firm has a market capitalization of $12.55 billion, a PE ratio of 20.18 and a beta of 1.16. Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd. has a 12-month low of $34.16 and a 12-month high of $56.29. 




Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings (NASDAQ:NCLH) last posted its earnings results on Wednesday, May 10th. The company reported $0.40 earnings per share for the quarter, topping the Zacks’ consensus estimate of $0.37 by $0.03. Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings had a net margin of 12.57% and a return on equity of 16.76%. The company had revenue of $1.15 billion for the quarter, compared to analyst estimates of $1.14 billion. During the same quarter in the prior year, the business posted $0.38 EPS. The firm’s revenue was up 6.8% compared to the same quarter last year.  On average, analysts forecast that  Norwegian Cruise Line Holdings Ltd. will post $3.88 EPS for the current fiscal year. 
